		<img width="2048" height="984" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="conservationists lift a sawfish into a truck" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth-1200x577.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-sawtooth-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">State and federal partners in the United States are racing to rescue smalltooth sawfish in Florida, where the fish are exhibiting unusual and concerning behavior, such as spinning and whirling. Photo courtesy of the Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Rescuers Grapple with How to Save Distressed Sawfish</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">In Florida, an effort is underway to bring endangered smalltooth sawfish to safety, following mysterious behaviors and deaths.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by Amy Green 								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						April 11, 2024 | 900 words, about 4 minutes					</aside>
				</header>

